The paper deals with rate-distortion theory, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves modeling and analyzing the behavior of multiple sources and receivers, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The use of side information and correlation between sources and side information suggests the subfield of source coding and channel coding with side information (cs.SI). The paper also involves analyzing and characterizing the rate-distortion region, which is a problem in optimization and decision making (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses some binary examples and intuitions, which suggests the subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
